{# Per-field unpack snippet inlined into the struct's unpack_from.

   Two paths:
   - "trivial" (not needs_validate, i.e. width is native 8/16/32/64): direct
     load + single static_cast. C++20 guarantees the uintN → intN conversion
     is two's-complement-safe, so no explicit sign-extension subtraction
     needed.
   - "complex" (needs_validate): non-native width. Mask-or-padding-check,
     then sign-extend if signed-short, then a single cast. The post-mask
     range check is tautological (mask + sign-extend produce in-range
     values by construction) so it's omitted. #}
